		<text id="50" type="text/plain" rect="(1011.400064824722, 2044.2204869224247, 295.6043956043957, 412.08791208791195)" font-family=".AppleSystemUIFont" font-size="16">AUC:

- measuers how well a model separates fraud and legitimate transactions overall


5 Fold Cross Validaton:

- tests the model 5 different times on different types of data
- more reliable and less bias
</text>
		<text id="51" type="text/plain" rect="(790.909090909091, 1670.688044831881, 378.4090909090909, 43.181818181818244)" font-family=".AppleSystemUIFont" font-size="16">——————————————————————————</text>
		<text id="52" type="text/plain" rect="(792.0454545454545, 1925.0, 404.5454545454546, 53.409090909090764)" font-family=".AppleSystemUIFont" font-size="16">———————————————————————————</text>
		<text id="53" type="text/plain" rect="(1206.1538461538457, 1384.6153846153843, 110.76923076923072, 32.30769230769238)" font-family=".AppleSystemUIFont" font-size="16">Uses AUC </text>
		<text id="54" type="text/plain" rect="(56.75675675675673, 1582.8828828828816, 168.46846846846847, 110.81081081081084)" font-family=".AppleSystemUIFont" font-size="16">GINI:

- measures how well a feature separates the data into pure groups

- pure = most of the data belongs to one class (Legit or Fraud)</text>
		<text id="55" type="text/plain" rect="(270.2702702702702, 1590.0900900900906, 266.66666666666674, 164.0)" font-family=".AppleSystemUIFont" font-size="16">ANOVA:

- compares the average value of a feature between legit and fraud transactions

- average is very different = strong feature</text>
	</annotations>
